01:32:14,660 --> 01:32:15,990
Good food.

816
01:32:19,790 --> 01:32:22,210
Radio Tokyo man 2: They have lovely food.

817
01:32:28,632 --> 01:32:29,972
You want to go back to camp?

818
01:32:33,971 --> 01:32:36,261
You make broadcast.

819
01:32:37,349 --> 01:32:38,679
(Sighs)

820
01:33:28,150 --> 01:33:30,440
You are like me.

821
01:33:31,361 --> 01:33:33,611
We are both strong.

822
01:33:34,865 --> 01:33:38,415
I saw it in your eyes...

823
01:33:38,493 --> 01:33:40,373
The first day.

824
01:33:41,371 --> 01:33:42,961
I thought...

825
01:33:43,040 --> 01:33:46,790
This man will be my friend.

826
01:33:49,671 --> 01:33:51,091
But...

827
01:33:51,673 --> 01:33:54,553
Enemy of Japan.

828
01:33:56,220 --> 01:33:58,260
You do not listen.

829
01:33:59,181 --> 01:34:02,391
You do not do
what is asked of you.

830
01:34:10,734 --> 01:34:14,074
It is necessary to have respect.

831
01:34:15,197 --> 01:34:16,527
No respect...

832
01:34:17,407 --> 01:34:19,157
No order.

833
01:34:25,582 --> 01:34:28,842
This man must be taught respect.

834
01:34:29,169 --> 01:34:33,419
All other prisoners will
teach him this lesson.

835
01:34:35,968 --> 01:34:37,968
Each prisoner...

836
01:34:38,595 --> 01:34:42,305
Will punch this man in his face.

837
01:34:48,230 --> 01:34:50,440
(Shouting in Japanese)

838
01:34:54,695 --> 01:34:56,115
Sir...

839
01:34:57,698 --> 01:34:59,528
We cannot do that.

840
01:35:04,288 --> 01:35:05,708
(Watanabe commands in Japanese)

841
01:35:34,651 --> 01:35:35,651
(Phil groans)

842
01:35:35,736 --> 01:35:37,336
(Watanabe continues
shouting in Japanese)

843
01:35:37,696 --> 01:35:39,066
Louie: Do it.

844
01:35:41,241 --> 01:35:43,581
Do it, sir. Come on.

845
01:35:44,661 --> 01:35:46,621
Just get it over with.

846
01:35:46,955 --> 01:35:49,495
Punch him in the face.

847
01:35:55,047 --> 01:35:56,417
Come on.

848
01:35:57,216 --> 01:35:58,756
Watanabe: Punch him!

849
01:36:04,014 --> 01:36:05,024
Next!

850
01:36:05,682 --> 01:36:07,062
Louie: Go on.

851
01:36:07,142 --> 01:36:08,942
Come on, come on.

852
01:36:14,525 --> 01:36:15,985
Next!

853
01:36:18,403 --> 01:36:20,663
Okay. Come on, come on, sir.

854
01:36:20,697 --> 01:36:22,527
Come on.

855
01:36:24,910 --> 01:36:26,040
- Hit hard!
- Come on!

856
01:36:26,078 --> 01:36:27,288
Hit me!

857
01:36:30,207 --> 01:36:31,367
Next!

858
01:36:33,210 --> 01:36:34,880
Come on, tink, hit me good. Go on.

859
01:36:35,754 --> 01:36:36,764
(Louie groans)

860
01:36:36,839 --> 01:36:38,209
Watanabe: Next!

861
01:36:39,341 --> 01:36:40,681
Louie: Come on.

862
01:36:40,717 --> 01:36:41,757
(Louie continues groaning)

863
01:36:41,844 --> 01:36:42,894
Watanabe: Next!

864
01:36:52,396 --> 01:36:54,186
Watanabe: Hit hard!

865
01:36:57,109 --> 01:36:58,609
Watanabe: Next!

866
01:37:06,410 --> 01:37:07,410
(Speaking in Japanese)

867
01:37:23,594 --> 01:37:25,104
Watanabe: Harder!

868
01:37:31,935 --> 01:37:33,095
Watanabe: Next!

869
01:37:39,610 --> 01:37:40,820
Watanabe: Next!

870
01:37:45,782 --> 01:37:47,282
Next!

871
01:37:58,086 --> 01:37:59,166
(Speaking in Japanese)

872
01:38:31,495 --> 01:38:33,875
(Guard keeping count in Japanese)

873
01:38:34,373 --> 01:38:36,923
(All keeping count in Japanese)

874
01:38:43,215 --> 01:38:45,385
(Men laughing)

875
01:38:47,302 --> 01:38:48,852
(Hooting and whistling)

876
01:38:49,513 --> 01:38:50,513
Tinker: (As stepsister 1) Cinderella!

877
01:38:50,556 --> 01:38:51,556
Miller: (As stepsister 2) Cinderella!

878
01:38:51,640 --> 01:38:53,350
Ah, cinderella!

879
01:38:53,392 --> 01:38:56,022
- Where is that naughty little maggot?
- (Laughter continues)

880
01:38:56,061 --> 01:38:57,691
Have you seen her, fella?

881
01:38:58,647 --> 01:39:00,357
Ah, there you are,
you lazy little girl.

882
01:39:00,440 --> 01:39:04,150
How am I supposed to get ready for the ball
with you sitting there doing nothing?

883
01:39:04,194 --> 01:39:05,534
Miller: (As stepsister 2)
That's as useful to us

884
01:39:05,612 --> 01:39:07,362
as our morning dance routines.

885
01:39:07,447 --> 01:39:08,867
(Laughter)

886
01:39:13,537 --> 01:39:14,867
Tinker: (As stepsister 1) Fix my dress

887
01:39:14,913 --> 01:39:17,963
so I can catch the eye
of the dreamy prince hillenbrand.

888
01:39:18,041 --> 01:39:20,631
You couldn't catch the eye of a prince
if it fell in your lap.

889
01:39:20,711 --> 01:39:22,881
Come, cinders, fix my hair.

890
01:39:24,715 --> 01:39:26,635
Tinker: (As stepsister 1) Fix my dress!

891
01:39:26,717 --> 01:39:27,877
Miller: (As stepsister 2) Fix my hair!

892
01:39:27,968 --> 01:39:29,048
Tinker: (As stepsister 1) Dress!

893
01:39:29,136 --> 01:39:30,716
Miller: (As stepsister 2) Hair, hair, hair!

894
01:39:30,762 --> 01:39:32,142
Tinker: (As stepsister 1)
Are you speaking kraut now?

895
01:39:32,222 --> 01:39:34,222
Fitzgerald: (As cinderella)
Enough! Enough!

896
01:39:34,266 --> 01:39:37,226
You guys make me do
all these stupid, impossible things

897
01:39:37,269 --> 01:39:39,349
with no food and no rest!

898
01:39:39,396 --> 01:39:41,816
You lock me up
in a rabbit hutch.

899
01:39:41,899 --> 01:39:43,399
I've had enough!

900
01:39:44,193 --> 01:39:45,903
(Whispering) I have good news.

901
01:39:49,114 --> 01:39:51,074
I have had a promotion.

902
01:39:51,742 --> 01:39:53,542
That's the good news.

903
01:39:55,204 --> 01:39:56,914
The bad news?

904
01:39:59,917 --> 01:40:02,417
I say goodbye to my friends.

905
01:40:09,635 --> 01:40:12,265
I leave omori tomorrow.

906
01:40:17,601 --> 01:40:21,401
Blackie: (As old lady)
Nothing in this life is hopeless, cinders.

907
01:40:21,438 --> 01:40:24,358
If you keep your
head and your heart

908
01:40:24,441 --> 01:40:27,691
you can do anything!

909
01:40:27,778 --> 01:40:29,198
(Men jeering and hooting)

910
01:40:29,279 --> 01:40:30,989
Fear not, dear child...

911
01:40:31,615 --> 01:40:34,285
I am your fairy godmother.

912
01:40:34,451 --> 01:40:36,621
You may congratulate me.

913
01:40:39,414 --> 01:40:40,584
Mmm.

914
01:40:47,214 --> 01:40:49,174
(Men applauding)

915
01:41:17,953 --> 01:41:20,333
And there he goes.

916
01:41:21,498 --> 01:41:23,498
Just like that.

917
01:41:38,182 --> 01:41:39,682
Miller: I have got...

918
01:41:40,517 --> 01:41:41,727
Four kings.

919
01:41:42,186 --> 01:41:43,516
And there you go.

920
01:41:44,688 --> 01:41:46,728
The baron's been beaten, tinker.

921
01:41:46,815 --> 01:41:48,565
- Tinker: Oh, yeah?
- Sugar for us tonight.

922
01:41:48,650 --> 01:41:50,990
(Indistinct chattering continues)

923
01:41:56,742 --> 01:41:58,202
(Exhales)

924
01:42:10,380 --> 01:42:13,050
(Alarm sirens blaring)

925
01:42:13,217 --> 01:42:15,047
(Men shouting)

926
01:42:15,219 --> 01:42:16,849
(Distant explosions)

927
01:42:22,726 --> 01:42:24,556
(Gunfire)

928
01:42:24,937 --> 01:42:26,687
(Shouting)

929
01:42:43,288 --> 01:42:44,408
Fitzgerald: Got it, Miller?

930
01:42:44,498 --> 01:42:45,668
Miller: Send another bucket!

931
01:42:54,550 --> 01:42:56,630
We're helping the japs now?

932
01:42:57,511 --> 01:42:58,931
Might as well let it burn.

933
01:42:59,012 --> 01:43:00,892
Pass it down!

934
01:43:02,182 --> 01:43:03,222
There you go.

935
01:43:06,770 --> 01:43:07,940
(Explosions continue)

936
01:43:17,322 --> 01:43:19,662
Tinker: B-29s, boys!

937
01:43:22,119 --> 01:43:23,699
Won't be long now.

938
01:43:24,204 --> 01:43:26,044
I wouldn't get too excited.

939
01:43:26,874 --> 01:43:29,134
If the allies win,

940
01:43:29,209 --> 01:43:31,589
the japs issue kill-all orders.

941
01:43:33,422 --> 01:43:35,472
I overheard them.

942
01:43:37,384 --> 01:43:39,724
We win, we're dead.

943
01:43:42,764 --> 01:43:45,854
Tinker: Well, what are we
supposed to be praying for?

944
01:43:47,019 --> 01:43:48,019
(Shrill whistle)

945
01:43:48,103 --> 01:43:49,313
Down! Get down!

946
01:43:54,193 --> 01:43:55,323
(Gasps)

947
01:43:55,360 --> 01:43:57,240
Grab your gear.
They're moving us out.

948
01:44:00,866 --> 01:44:03,116
- To where?
- I don't know.

949
01:44:03,160 --> 01:44:04,660
Some new camp.

950
01:44:05,162 --> 01:44:06,832
Tokyo ritz.

951
01:44:06,914 --> 01:44:09,334
Some place the
allies can't find us.

952
01:44:12,461 --> 01:44:13,801
(Guard ordering in Japanese)

953
01:45:14,439 --> 01:45:16,109
(Sobbing)

954
01:46:27,179 --> 01:46:29,009
(Guards ordering in Japanese)

955
01:47:01,505 --> 01:47:03,555
(Guard continues
ordering in Japanese)

956
01:47:47,718 --> 01:47:48,928
(Door slams shut)

957
01:48:13,160 --> 01:48:14,410
(Guard ordering in Japanese)

958
01:48:25,214 --> 01:48:28,054
This is naoetsu prison camp.

959
01:48:29,760 --> 01:48:33,260
I am sergeant watanabe,

960
01:48:33,305 --> 01:48:35,435
your commanding officer.

961
01:48:36,808 --> 01:48:41,188
You are enemies of Japan.

962
01:48:42,105 --> 01:48:44,185
You will be treated...

963
01:48:45,359 --> 01:48:47,439
Accordingly.

964
01:48:50,197 --> 01:48:52,657
You will help the Japanese

965
01:48:52,741 --> 01:48:55,371
by working on the coal barges.

966
01:48:55,869 --> 01:48:59,409
Anyone who will not work...

967
01:49:00,916 --> 01:49:02,746
Will be executed.

968
01:49:12,344 --> 01:49:14,684
Why don't you
look me in the eye?

969
01:49:21,478 --> 01:49:23,148
Clift: You boys can sleep here.

970
01:49:27,234 --> 01:49:28,744
You two over there.

971
01:49:35,534 --> 01:49:37,334
This is the end, mates.

972
01:49:37,995 --> 01:49:39,415
No one knows you're here.

973
01:49:41,498 --> 01:49:43,668
It's best if you
just resign to your fate.

974
01:50:38,263 --> 01:50:39,393
(Groans)

975
01:50:41,850 --> 01:50:43,560
(Screaming)

976
01:51:11,004 --> 01:51:12,384
(Ordering in Japanese)

977
01:51:16,593 --> 01:51:17,933
(Commanding in Japanese)

978
01:51:22,766 --> 01:51:25,516
Your president Roosevelt

979
01:51:28,480 --> 01:51:29,690
is dead.

980
01:51:44,079 --> 01:51:45,209
(Sobbing)

981
01:51:56,133 --> 01:51:57,843
(Officers ordering in Japanese)

982
01:52:06,935 --> 01:52:08,555
(Groaning)

983
01:52:35,339 --> 01:52:36,509
(Ordering in Japanese)

984
01:52:47,643 --> 01:52:48,983
Louie?

985
01:52:53,565 --> 01:52:55,025
Louie?

986
01:52:58,362 --> 01:52:59,572
Are you all right?

987
01:53:26,223 --> 01:53:27,773
(Officer commanding in Japanese)

988
01:53:41,655 --> 01:53:43,245
(Panting)

989
01:53:52,624 --> 01:53:53,964
(Officer shouting in Japanese)

990
01:54:14,730 --> 01:54:16,150
(Speaking in Japanese)

991
01:54:23,906 --> 01:54:25,276
Pick up!

992
01:55:00,734 --> 01:55:01,824
Watanabe: Lift it.

993
01:55:04,655 --> 01:55:05,785
Lift it!

994
01:55:36,687 --> 01:55:38,017
Over your head.

995
01:56:03,672 --> 01:56:05,012
If he drops it

996
01:56:06,049 --> 01:56:07,089
shoot him.

997
01:56:50,844 --> 01:56:52,184
(Breath wavering)

998
01:57:01,939 --> 01:57:03,899
(Officers ordering in Japanese)

999
01:58:04,334 --> 01:58:05,964
Come on, Louie.

1000
01:58:07,004 --> 01:58:08,464
Come on, boy.

1001
01:58:13,802 --> 01:58:15,222
Come on, Louie.

1002
01:58:48,629 --> 01:58:50,049
(Grunts)

1003
01:58:50,130 --> 01:58:51,460
(Yelling)

1004
01:58:55,761 --> 01:58:56,891
(Laughing)

1005
01:58:57,554 --> 01:58:58,894
(Yells)

1006
01:59:04,561 --> 01:59:05,941
(Breathing heavily)

1007
01:59:14,488 --> 01:59:15,858
Don't look at me.

1008
01:59:18,408 --> 01:59:20,078
(Voice breaks) Don't look at me.

1009
01:59:23,372 --> 01:59:24,872
(Watanabe speaking in Japanese)

1010
01:59:37,261 --> 01:59:38,681
Don't look at me!

1011
01:59:39,096 --> 01:59:40,886
Don't look at me!

1012
02:00:24,266 --> 02:00:25,636
(Breathing heavily)

1013
02:00:57,966 --> 02:00:59,546
(Commanding in Japanese)

1014
02:01:06,058 --> 02:01:07,348
(Shouting in Japanese)

1015
02:01:40,050 --> 02:01:41,260
(Guard commanding in Japanese)

1016
02:01:45,931 --> 02:01:48,731
(Officer speaking in Japanese)

1017
02:01:55,816 --> 02:01:58,356
Fitzgerald: (Translating)
"Prisoners of naoetsu...

1018
02:01:59,194 --> 02:02:03,034
"The war has come
to a point of cessation.

1019
02:02:06,410 --> 02:02:09,330
(Officer continues in Japanese)

1020
02:02:21,758 --> 02:02:23,128
Fitzgerald: "Today...

1021
02:02:23,218 --> 02:02:27,348
"In the spirit of the new future
of our great nations,

1022
02:02:28,807 --> 02:02:34,597
"we invite all prisoners
to bathe in the hokura river."

1023
02:02:37,441 --> 02:02:39,111
(Officer commanding in Japanese)

1024
02:02:40,485 --> 02:02:41,775
This is it.

1025
02:02:43,780 --> 02:02:44,950
We're dead.

1026
02:02:47,075 --> 02:02:49,035
(Guard ordering in Japanese)

1027
02:04:11,034 --> 02:04:12,454
(Guard continues ordering)

1028
02:04:32,139 --> 02:04:35,059
(Distant engine droning)

1029
02:05:21,563 --> 02:05:23,693
Tinker: That's our boys!
That's our boys!

1030
02:05:23,774 --> 02:05:25,324
Miller: They've seen us!

1031
02:05:25,400 --> 02:05:28,450
It's over!
The war is over!

1032
02:05:29,071 --> 02:05:31,201
(All cheering)

1033
02:06:39,474 --> 02:06:41,024
(Talking indistinctly)

1034
02:08:37,301 --> 02:08:39,391
(People cheering)

1035
02:08:48,312 --> 02:08:49,312
Pete: Louie!

1036
02:09:08,832 --> 02:09:10,502
You made it.

1037
02:09:10,792 --> 02:09:12,792
Oh, God, look at you.

1038
02:09:14,922 --> 02:09:16,672
(Both laughing)

1039
02:09:19,468 --> 02:09:21,258
Oh, mama.

1040
02:10:52,978 --> 02:10:55,358
(People cheering and applauding)

1041
02:11:04,114 --> 02:11:05,994
(Cheering continues)

